Combining two 'grown super-mutant' items of the same size but different habitats (e.g., medium land + medium water) yields 55. Combining 'grown super-mutant' items of *different sizes* and different habitats (e.g., medium water + large land) yields an even higher value of 60. Avoid further tool use on 'grown super-mutant' items (e.g., double growth or triple mutation) as it drastically reduces value or corrupts the item. Also, combining raw ingredients with processed ones, especially if they are different sizes, often leads to very low values (-70 or worse).

message: To achieve high scores, the most reliable strategy is to select one ingredient and apply the mutation catalyst twice, then the growth serum once. This sequence consistently yields an item worth 25-30 points. A second application of growth serum on this item *might* increase the value further (e.g., to 30-35) but can also cause a significant value drop (e.g., to 0-10), so use with caution. When combining items, prioritize ingredients that share the same 'lives in' environment (e.g., two 'lives on land' items) to create a base item, then apply growth serum once or twice to it for 15-25 points. Crucially, avoid applying the mutation catalyst to complex, combined, or already super-mutant/grown items, as this consistently results in 'corrupted' features and extremely negative values. Also, refrain from combining high-value complex items with low-value, feature-diverse items, as this tends to create 'overcomplicated' items with disastrously low scores.
